---
import PageLayout from '../layouts/PageLayout.astro';
---

<PageLayout title="About | Travis Carter" description="Senior Software Engineer & Architect focused on distributed systems, event-driven architectures, and developer platforms.">
  <section class="section-spacing px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 max-w-6xl mx-auto">
    <h1 class="mb-6">About</h1>

    <!-- Intro -->
    <div data-animate="fade" class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-8 items-start mb-8">
      <div>
        <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-text-secondary)] leading-relaxed max-w-3xl">
          I'm Travis Carter, a self-taught Senior Software Engineer & Architect who built two
          careers the same way &mdash; by learning on the job and pushing higher. I spent a decade
          in civil engineering before teaching myself to code during the Great Recession, and I've
          been building distributed systems, streaming platforms, and cloud infrastructure ever since.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Impact Metrics -->
    <div data-animate="slide-up" class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-4 my-8">
      <div class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-5 text-center">
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-accent)]">83%</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mt-1">Build time reduction</p>
      </div>
      <div class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-5 text-center">
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-accent)]">100+</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mt-1">Services migrated, zero downtime</p>
      </div>
      <div class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-5 text-center">
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold font-[var(--font-heading)] text-[var(--color-accent)]">4+</p>
        <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)] mt-1">Industries, one streaming engine</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Career Journey -->
    <div data-animate="slide-up" class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="mb-2">Career Journey</h2>
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <div data-animate="slide-up" data-animate-delay="1" class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-5 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-accent)]">
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Sr. Software Engineer &mdash; ECFX</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Oct 2023 &ndash; Present</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Full-stack engineer and platform architect at a law-tech startup. Sole owner of DevOps and infrastructure.
            Refactored CI/CD pipelines to cut build times from 45 minutes to under 10 with selective build and deploy.
            Upgraded a six-year-old codebase to Micronaut 4 and Hibernate 6, and introduced Claude Code workflows
            that accelerated the team's development velocity.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-animate="slide-up" data-animate-delay="2" class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-5 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-cat-architecture)]">
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Director of Platform Engineering &mdash; PHC</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Oct 2021 &ndash; Mar 2024</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Led platform engineering at a health-tech Series A startup during the pandemic. Owned architecture,
            system design, and the development roadmap. Built a real-time risk anomaly detection and notification
            platform from scratch using Flink, Elasticsearch, Protobufs, and Micronaut. Created a custom Flink
            StateFun mixed-language framework for processors in Java and Python.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-animate="slide-up" data-animate-delay="3" class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-5 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-cat-infrastructure)]">
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Sr. Software Engineer &mdash; Globality</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Oct 2020 &ndash; Oct 2021</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Implemented Kubernetes cluster architecture and deployed vCluster (Loft) to give the engineering team
            sandboxed development environments, improving developer workflow across a 20-person engineering org.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-animate="slide-up" data-animate-delay="4" class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-5 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-accent)]">
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Sr. Software Engineer &mdash; Banjo</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Aug 2014 &ndash; Aug 2020</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Six formative years at a fast-paced startup building real-time event processing and anomaly detection
            systems. Built an automation API that cut discovery-to-notification times from 7 minutes to under
            30 seconds. Created an inter-agency code coordination framework for law enforcement, fire, and safety
            agencies. Worked across the full stack &mdash; Flink, Kafka, Elasticsearch, Java, Ruby, Python &mdash;
            in an environment where everyone shared knowledge and owned everything.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-animate="slide-up" class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-5 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-cat-architecture)]">
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Frontend Developer</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">Nov 2011 &ndash; Aug 2014</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Early software career building JavaScript SPAs and UX. Rewrote an ASP.NET site into a true
            single-page application using Knockout.js and Durandal.js.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-animate="slide-up" class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-5 border-l-4 border-[var(--color-cat-infrastructure)]">
          <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center sm:justify-between mb-2">
            <h3 class="text-base font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)]">Civil Engineering Draftsman &amp; Project Designer</h3>
            <span class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-muted)]">2001 &ndash; 2011</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            A decade of plan creation, project design, and engineering approvals. Drafted plans for Big Horn
            Golf Course in Palm Springs, designed the Blue Diamond shopping complex in Las Vegas, and trained
            engineers in Dubai on Autodesk Civil 3D for the Palm Islands project. Self-taught AutoCAD before
            graduating high school. When the 2008 recession hit, taught myself to code and pivoted to software.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- What I Do -->
    <div data-animate="slide-up" class="prose mt-16">
      <h2>What I Do</h2>
      <p>
        Most senior engineers have spent their career in one area of the stack. I've spent meaningful
        time in all of them &mdash; platform, frontend, data, DevOps, infrastructure. My work spans
        the full lifecycle of complex systems, from architecture design through deployment and
        optimization. I'm particularly drawn to problems at the boundaries between systems:
        event-driven architectures, streaming pipelines, and the tooling that makes teams productive.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Technical Expertise -->
    <div data-animate="slide-up" class="mt-16">
      <h2 class="mb-6">Technical Expertise</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div data-animate="slide-up" data-animate-delay="1" class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-2">Languages & Frameworks</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Java, Kotlin, TypeScript, Python. Micronaut, Spring Boot, Astro, React.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-animate="slide-up" data-animate-delay="2" class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-2">Data & Streaming</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Apache Kafka, Apache Flink, Elasticsearch, PostgreSQL, Protocol Buffers.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-animate="slide-up" data-animate-delay="3" class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-2">Infrastructure</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            AWS, Kubernetes (EKS), Terraform, Docker, GitLab CI, GitHub Actions.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div data-animate="slide-up" data-animate-delay="4" class="glass-panel rounded-lg p-4">
          <h3 class="text-sm font-semibold text-[var(--color-text-primary)] mb-2">Practices</h3>
          <p class="text-sm text-[var(--color-text-secondary)]">
            Domain-Driven Design, Event Sourcing, TDD, Observability, Platform Engineering.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Open Source -->
    <div data-animate="slide-up" class="prose mt-16">
      <h2>Open Source</h2>
      <p>
        I maintain several open-source libraries on Maven Central, including tools for
        Protocol Buffer testing, Elasticsearch integrations, and Micronaut extensions.
        I believe in building reusable, well-tested abstractions that help other developers
        move faster.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Philosophy -->
    <div data-animate="slide-up" class="prose mt-16">
      <h2>Philosophy</h2>
      <p>
        I believe the best engineering comes from deeply understanding the problem before
        reaching for solutions. I value simplicity, clear boundaries, and systems that
        are easy to reason about. When something breaks at 3 AM, the architecture should
        make the root cause obvious.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Get in Touch -->
    <div data-animate="fade" class="prose mt-16">
      <h2>Get in Touch</h2>
      <p>
        I'm always open to discussing distributed systems challenges, platform engineering,
        and interesting technical problems. Reach out via
        <a href="mailto:hello@phatjam98.com">email</a>,
        connect on <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/travis-carter/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">LinkedIn</a>,
        or check out my work on <a href="https://github.com/phatjam98" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</PageLayout>
